      "comment": "Just four left post scratchings which will likely see a tactical affair. RADICAL DUDE (4) is a gelding by Farnan on debut for the Freedman yard. He's looked good at the jumpouts, coming away to win his latest well. Looks ready to go and can measure up first time of asking. WYANDRA (5) didn't fire first up at Caulfield Heath but that looked a stronger race, battling away to finish seventh in a good maiden. He can do much better here with that run under the belt. ADAVALE (6) is a filly by Magnus on debut for the Moody & Coleman yard. She's jumped out okay. DISCOVER LUPINO (1) is a gelding by Overshare on debut for the Cliff Brown yard who can also run well.",
